        "text": [
          ": مَنْ کَانَتْ قِرَاءَتُهُ فِی فَرَائِضِهِ بِ السَّماءِ وَ الطَّارِقِ کَانَتْ لَهُ عِنْدَ اللَّهِ یَوْمَ الْقِیَامَهِ جَاهٌ وَ مَنْزِلَهٌ وَ کَانَ مِنْ رُفَقَاءِ النَّبِیِّینَ وَ أَصْحَابِهِمْ فِی الْجَنَّهِ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.sayed-athar-husain-rizvi-&-sayed-maqsood-athar": [
            "1. From the previous chain from al-Hussain from his father from al-Mu’ala b. Khunays from Abi Abdillah (a.s.) who said: Whoever recites Surah Tariq in his obligatory prayer would enjoy great prestige and position before Allah on the Day of Judgment and he would be among the friends of the prophets and their companions in Paradise."
          ]
